    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-05-15T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-05-15T10:00:00-05:00" n="502"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d502">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.75 National Telephone Company/169:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Spain (<persName type="from">Flack</persName>)
                        to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-05-15T15:00:00+00:00"
                            >May 15, 1933—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 15—1:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>20. Learn from Rock that he has sent important communications to his principals
                    concerning indirect efforts to impair telephone contract.</p>
                <p>In the absence of specific instructions I shall reiterate our position enunciated
                    last year<note n="16" xml:id="d502fn16">See telegram No. 90, November 23, 1932,
                        from the Ambassador in Spain, <ref target="frus1932v02#pg_566">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1932, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 566</ref>.</note> should action be
                    required.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Flack</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
